Function: algisdivision
Section: algebras
C-Name: algisdivision
Prototype: iGDG
Help: algisdivision(al,{pl}): test whether the central simple algebra al is a
 division algebra at the place pl, or globally if pl is not set.
Doc: Given a central simple algebra \var{al} output by \tet{alginit} and a prime
 ideal or an integer between $1$ and $r_1+r_2$, tests whether \var{al} is a
 division algebra locally at the place specified by \var{pl}. If \var{pl} is not
 set, tests whether \var{al} is (globally) a division algebra.
 \bprog
 ? nf = nfinit(y^2-5);
 ? A = alginit(nf, [-1,y]);
 ? algisdivision(A, 1)
 %3 = 1
 ? algisdivision(A, 2)
 %4 = 0
 ? algisdivision(A, idealprimedec(nf,2)[1])
 %5 = 1
 ? algisdivision(A, idealprimedec(nf,5)[1])
 %6 = 0
 ? algisdivision(A)
 %7 = 1
 @eprog
